{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cbc64371-7ccc-4b03-8e05-a849b0a6805f","content":"Here are the **evaluation performance issues** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. File I/O Property Function (High Impact)\n**Line 13 in `EvalHeavy.csproj`:**\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nProperty functions that perform file I/O execute during evaluation (before any build targets run). This blocks the evaluation phase with disk access. **Fix:** Read the file in a target at execution time instead, or use a build task.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Overly Broad Glob Pattern (Medium Impact)\n**Line 9:**\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` walks the entire directory tree during evaluation. If this project grows or sits near large directories (e.g., `node_modules`, artifacts), evaluation time will spike. **Fix:** Use `DefaultItemExcludes` to exclude known large directories, or narrow the glob to specific extensions/paths.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deep Import Chain (Low-Medium Impact)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nA 3-level chain is manageable, but this pattern doesn't scale. Each additional import level adds file reads and increases preprocessing complexity. In larger projects this can exceed 20 levels and measurably slow evaluation. **Fix:** Flatten where possible; consolidate into fewer files.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Issue | Severity | Fix |\n|-------|----------|-----|\n| `File::ReadAllText` during eval | 🔴 High | Move to a target/task |\n| `**\\*.*` glob | 🟡 Medium | Narrow pattern or add exclusions |\n| Nested import chain | 🟢 Low | Flatten imports |\n\nThe most impactful fix is removing the `System.IO.File::ReadAllText` call from the property evaluation phase.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"303ba6a6-177c-4720-a003-20512a841ad8","outputTokens":483,"requestId":"F021:5F08B:1325DA6:15A95AD:69F94591"},"id":"252befbe-016